    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Saint Paul</placeName>
                <date>May the 6—<add>שושן פורים</add>, 5623</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Revd Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I send you here an article, I<lb/> consider it worthy to have a
                place in your valuable Occident, But<lb/> after all I leave it to your own
                    <sic>judgement</sic>, do with it what you think<lb/> best, as I have no patience
                to write with carefulness, and you are all<lb/> ready acquainted with my bad
                writing, you will understand well<lb/> my meaning, and you will be so kind to
                arrange it, and correct it as<lb/> it ought to be, <add>יראו רשעים יבושו
                    ויכלמו</add>, besides I hope it will answer to the<lb/> Christians as well for
                their accusation, with which they accuse us<lb/> being superstitious in not
                pronouncing the holy name. Should the doctor<lb/> say any thing against it, with the
                help of the Almighty we will be<lb/> able to answer him and to bruise his head. Any
                how, I would like to<lb/> know your opinion about what I have written, till
                then,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">I remain, Dear and Revd Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">your wisher, one who loves you as himself</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">E. Marcuson</persName>.</p>
            <p>If you will be please to write to me, write in care of <persName>Mr.
                    Cardza.</persName></p>
        </body>
    </text>
